                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "A creature that is reduced to 0 Hit Points by a void dragon\u2019s bite attack must spend 1 Resolve point or be immediately slain and reduced to dust.",
                "name": "Obliterate",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "Instead of a cone of cold, a void dragon can breathe a 30-foot cone of energy that suffocates those it touches. Air-breathing creatures within the cone must succeed at a Fortitude save or begin attempting Constitution checks to avoid <a aonid=\"Environmental Rules\" category=\"Environment\" game-obj=\"Rules\">suffocation</a>, even if they have environmental protections.<br/><br/> An affected creature can attempt a new Fortitude saving throw at the beginning of each turn to shake off this effect and regain its air supply.",
